Ad Text:
At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members. We are dedicated to building a high-performance environment underpinned by a strong risk culture, ensuring we deliver the best outcomes for our members.

Make a difference delivering outcomes for our millions of members
Build analytics tools for Dealing, Treasury, Exposure Management, and Risk
Permanent role located in Melbourne or Sydney

Your new role

This role builds and delivers analytics solutions, including tools, models and measurement, that operationalise methodologies defined by Liquidity & Implementation (L&I) Subject Matter Experts (SMEs). The solutions support core Dealing, Treasury, Exposure Management, and Risk functions, and require a strong grasp of front-office operations and data flows.

Working closely with SMEs, Technology and Data teams, the role translates business and analytical requirements into robust, testable and well‑documented technical solutions. These solutions are delivered using the Fund's authorised technology stack and approved integrations with investment and treasury platforms.

Key responsibilities include:

Building and implementing solutions that support core Treasury (including liquidity and cashflow management), and Implementation (including rebalancing, transitions and execution) use cases, using L&I SME-defined methodologies, including data models, calculation logic, analytics tools, and reporting architecture aligned to approved standards;
Working closely with SMEs and/or Technology Team to define non-functional requirements for solutions (performance, scalability, supportability, security, auditability) and implement appropriate controls;
Working with SMEs, Technology, and Data teams to deliver a prioritised pipeline of L&I tool and model work through agreed intake and governance processes;
Communicating progress, risks, and technical constraints clearly; escalate data or requirement issues to SME owners promptly;
Building, testing and maintaining analytics solutions based on SME-defined objectives and constraints;
Developing and maintaining Python/SQL-based calculation logic and reusable components to enable consistent, repeatable delivery across multiple use cases;
Producing clear technical documentation (logic, data lineage, dependencies, assumptions as provided by SMEs, operating procedures) to support transparency and handover;
Building controlled off-platform tooling (where appropriate and approved) such as automation scripts, utilities, and governed spreadsheet tooling, ensuring security, documentation and supportability.

What You'll Need

Demonstrated hands‑on experience building and deploying analytical or quantitative solutions within investment, markets or treasury environments, with a strong working understanding of front‑office Treasury, Dealing and Exposure Management workflows;
Prior first line experience across a range of stress testing, assumption calibration, collateral and counterparty exposure management, and pre and post trade risk analytics is desirable;
Advanced Python and SQL skills, including writing testable, performant code and reusable components for quantitative analytics and model implementation;
Strong experience with Microsoft Fabric (or equivalent) for data pipelines, transformations and calculation frameworks; ability to deliver repeatable, auditable and well-controlled analytics outputs;
Strong Power BI capability to build governed dashboards/reports with traceability to source data and calculation logic;
Applied machine learning/statistical modelling experience, ideally including Azure Machine Learning (or equivalent MLOps tooling) for model training, validation, deployment and monitoring;
Experience integrating analytics solutions with front-office / treasury platforms (e.g., Aladdin, Calypso or equivalents) using approved interfaces (APIs/file workflows) and secure access patterns;
Working familiarity across Liquidity & Implementation use cases (e.g., dealing/execution analytics, exposure management, cash/collateral analytics, counterparty utilisation, securities lending, balance sheet/liquidity reporting) to translate briefs into robust technical solutions;
Strong engineering discipline and delivery practices (version control, code review, testing, documentation, release/change processes, and production support/incident triage);
Collaborative communicator able to work effectively across SMEs, Technology and Data teams, managing expectations and surfacing constraints/risks early.

Life at AustralianSuper

AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.

What's Next

Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.

AustralianSuper uses AI to review resumes and conduct initial phone interviews. This involves processing your resume, cover letter, and voice recording in Australia and the USA to help assess your suitability for the applied role. When invited to an AI phone screening, you may opt for a traditional phone screening instead. For information on how we handle your personal data, please refer to our Candidate Privacy Policy.

https://www.australiansuper.com/careers/candidate-privacy-notice

Australian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.

Agencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by AustralianSuper's Talent Acquisition team. We will contact our preferred agency partners should we require additional support. Thank you.
